    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\nNO\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.8.0-dev-1024-ga220650fd6\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\nRecently, I've found that if we `set cmdheight=0`, these two options will be hidden and cannot use statusline to reshow.\r\n\r\n> [ 73/87 ] and 24\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97107165/188440671-945e2404-7959-46fc-8d77-3741102b3d41.png)\r\n\r\nAnd it seems statusline does not have any config options `%f %c etc` that can reshow these two options.\r\n\r\nThis is very inconvenient when we need to know how much char I have selected in visual mode and how many search results in `cmdheight=0`\r\n\r\nbtw: if the search result can be dynamic like `[ 1/11 ] [ 2/11 ] [ 3/11 ] ...`, it would be better :D\r\n\r\nbest wishes.\r\n",
